{
  "texts": [
    "Steven Geisz delves deeper, proposing that under specific conditions, there may be a moral obligation to cast a tactical vote (Geisz 2006).",
    "We share this more positive outlook on tactical voting.",
    "We hold that polling results crucially contribute to voter's knowledge-and that voters have an interest in more granular and frequent results for tactical voting purposes.",
    "Artificial intelligence enables this in a way that traditional polling cannot.",
    "In what follows, we expose and critically engage with Alvin Goldman's account of 'core voter knowledge' in electoral democracy (Goldman 2002) and provide a revised account which includes strategic knowledge."
  ]
}